That's it.

716
00:46:13,187 --> 00:46:16,022
Hey, who has opposable thumbs? Anybody?

717
00:46:20,903 --> 00:46:23,946
You want to try this one?
Make sure it's straight.

718
00:46:24,031 --> 00:46:25,615
This is awesome!
This is so cool.

719
00:46:25,699 --> 00:46:27,700
Here we go.
Oh, my God!

720
00:46:28,118 --> 00:46:31,370
Yeah. Gotta do the dance.
Come on, let's do the dance.

721
00:46:32,706 --> 00:46:34,540
- We're doing the dance.
Dylan, come on. Do the dance.

722
00:46:34,625 --> 00:46:37,376
Come on, do the dance.
I'm not doing the dance.

723
00:46:41,507 --> 00:46:43,716
- Don't scratch!
- Stop it. Come here.

724
00:46:43,801 --> 00:46:47,303
Insult to injury! My!

725
00:46:47,387 --> 00:46:49,430
- Good boy.
- Okay, guys. A little bit more.

726
00:46:49,515 --> 00:46:52,517
Here we go. I got it. Keep it... That's it!

727
00:46:53,560 --> 00:46:54,811
Beautiful!

728
00:46:59,900 --> 00:47:02,485
You guys all right?
Yup.

729
00:47:19,837 --> 00:47:20,920
"G."

730
00:47:40,232 --> 00:47:43,192
Well, I hope this isn't our last supper.

731
00:47:43,277 --> 00:47:46,153
There's no sign
of our heat wave breaking,

732
00:47:46,238 --> 00:47:48,030
so this dry, hot weather will continue.

733
00:47:48,115 --> 00:47:51,033
Until September 22, midday.

734
00:47:51,118 --> 00:47:54,245
If the ark isn't finished by then, you will be.

735
00:47:54,621 --> 00:47:57,957
Is that when it's going to happen?
September 22, midday?

736
00:47:58,041 --> 00:48:00,376
High temperatures
tomorrow back into the 90s everywhere,

737
00:48:00,460 --> 00:48:01,627
right on through Tuesday

738
00:48:01,712 --> 00:48:05,214
and the next seven days,
no showers, no storms.

739
00:48:05,299 --> 00:48:09,468
That would be a good day to have chicken.
How about Mom's chicken?

740
00:48:09,553 --> 00:48:13,222
Hon, could we have some more chicken
September 22, midday?

741
00:48:13,891 --> 00:48:17,268
Boys, will you excuse us, please?
Your father and I need to have a little talk.

742
00:48:17,352 --> 00:48:18,895
Busted.

743
00:48:18,979 --> 00:48:21,647
Dad, you're busted.
- Yeah, I know.

744
00:48:23,275 --> 00:48:25,943
- What are you doing?
- Do we have anything unleavened?

745
00:48:26,028 --> 00:48:29,572
Yeah, we do, it's in the back,
next to the frankincense and myrrh.

746
00:48:29,656 --> 00:48:32,825
We have a fancy name for it in this century,
it's called pita.

747
00:48:33,410 --> 00:48:37,705
- Got it.
- Evan, what is happening to you?

748
00:48:37,789 --> 00:48:41,125
Don't! No! Just put it down! Look at you.

749
00:48:41,209 --> 00:48:46,631
The hair. Are you on something?
Is it a mega-growth hormone? What?

750
00:48:48,216 --> 00:48:49,884
Evan, talk to me.

751
00:48:58,310 --> 00:49:00,144
I'm building an ark.

752
00:49:01,897 --> 00:49:03,689
What does that mean?

753
00:49:05,108 --> 00:49:09,070
God appeared to me
and told me to build an ark.

754
00:49:09,154 --> 00:49:13,074
He said there was going to be a flood
and that I should be prepared.

755
00:49:13,158 --> 00:49:15,618
Whenever I shave,
my beard grows right back out.

756
00:49:15,702 --> 00:49:20,748
My hair grows longer every day.
This robe... God sent me the robe.

757
00:49:20,832 --> 00:49:23,125
He thought it would be funny.

758
00:49:23,210 --> 00:49:27,964
I actually think it's really comfortable.
That's why I'm wearing it.

759
00:49:29,716 --> 00:49:32,218
The beard, the robe.

760
00:49:33,303 --> 00:49:34,720
You're Noah?

761
00:49:36,306 --> 00:49:38,265
Yeah, kind of.

762
00:49:38,350 --> 00:49:40,685
- Mom!
- Not now, Noah!

763
00:49:42,104 --> 00:49:44,230
- Dylan.
- Okay.

764
00:49:47,818 --> 00:49:51,278
We left everything behind to come here.

765
00:49:51,363 --> 00:49:55,116
Maybe that's put too much pressure on you.
I don't know.

766
00:49:55,200 --> 00:49:59,662
But this has got to stop. Please.
You're scaring me.

767
00:49:59,746 --> 00:50:04,417
The boys need their father back,
and I need my husband back.

768
00:50:21,643 --> 00:50:24,603
Yes. Successful. Powerful.
Handsome. Happy.

769
00:50:24,688 --> 00:50:27,523
Successful. Powerful. Handsome. Happy.

770
00:50:37,075 --> 00:50:38,576
Good morning!

771
00:50:43,457 --> 00:50:45,082
Cold today, huh?

772
00:50:56,470 --> 00:50:57,720
"Back to work"?

773
00:51:01,308 --> 00:51:06,979
Okay. All right. You want me
to wear the robe? I'll wear the robe.

774
00:51:08,023 --> 00:51:11,317
Two can play this game.

775
00:51:21,995 --> 00:51:23,996
Pice de rsistance.

776
00:51:25,916 --> 00:51:28,459
The student has become the teacher.

777
00:51:32,839 --> 00:51:34,256
This meeting will come to order.

778
00:51:34,341 --> 00:51:35,591
Rita, any sign of him?

779
00:51:35,675 --> 00:51:37,968
Marty, I told you,
I will let you know as soon as...

780
00:51:38,053 --> 00:51:41,347
You know what? You got me. He's here.
We're in the middle of a yoga class.

781
00:51:41,431 --> 00:51:43,265
Rita, this is no time forjokes.
I'm not kidding.

782
00:51:43,350 --> 00:51:45,726
If he's not in that meeting,
we're all out of a job.

783
00:51:45,811 --> 00:51:48,479
Wait a minute.
Let me finish my sun salutation.

784
00:51:53,401 --> 00:51:58,864
- Marty! Sorry I'm late. Come on, let's go.
- What is that?

785
00:51:58,949 --> 00:52:02,576
Making lemonade out of lemons.
Pick up your phone! Come on!

786
00:52:02,661 --> 00:52:05,955
At its heart,
this bill gives private citizens access

787
00:52:06,039 --> 00:52:08,082
to lands they technically already own.

788
00:52:08,166 --> 00:52:09,792
Will the Chairman yield?

789
00:52:09,876 --> 00:52:12,128
- Oh, look, there he is.
- Yup, yup, I see him.

790
00:52:12,212 --> 00:52:16,132
Access is just a word you're using
to hide what's really going on here.

791
00:52:16,216 --> 00:52:18,759
This is about development,
short and simple.

792
00:52:18,844 --> 00:52:23,973
Evan, what are you doing?
You have a pony tail on your face!

793
00:52:24,057 --> 00:52:26,433
What you gonna do next?
Cornrow your eyebrows?

794
00:52:26,518 --> 00:52:29,145
Development means
the advancement ofjobs,

795
00:52:29,229 --> 00:52:32,857
an increase in domestic commerce.
If you happen to like those things,

796
00:52:32,941 --> 00:52:37,319
I invite you to join myself and
my cosponsors, Congressman Dodd,

797
00:52:39,531 --> 00:52:41,448
Congressman Hughes

798
00:52:42,742 --> 00:52:44,493
and Congressman Baxter.

799
00:53:05,765 --> 00:53:07,808
Did you just do a wardrobe change?

800
00:53:07,893 --> 00:53:10,895
What do you think this is, the Oscars?
You are not Whoopi.

801
00:53:12,105 --> 00:53:14,481
Ladies and gentlemen! Please!

802
00:53:15,650 --> 00:53:19,695
Please! Congressman Baxter has a tendency
to embrace the theatrical

803
00:53:19,779 --> 00:53:22,448
in his support of this bill.
Congressman, let me warn you,

804
00:53:22,532 --> 00:53:26,035
you are approximately 10 seconds away
from committee censure.

805
00:53:26,119 --> 00:53:29,663
Oh, no. Hey, would anyone mind
if I close the window?

806
00:53:58,818 --> 00:54:03,072
Ladies and gentlemen! Please!
These animals are trained!

807
00:54:03,156 --> 00:54:04,907
I've seen this circus act before!

808
00:54:04,991 --> 00:54:07,910
Congressman, I'm sure St. Francis
would be envious.

809
00:54:08,036 --> 00:54:11,622
We, however, are not.
You have five seconds.

810
00:54:11,706 --> 00:54:14,541
You march yourself and your
little animal troupe out of here now

811
00:54:14,626 --> 00:54:16,502
or you will be forcibly removed.

812
00:54:16,586 --> 00:54:20,005
- I'm afraid I can't do that, sir.
- Congressman!

813
00:54:20,090 --> 00:54:23,425
- These animals are not trained.
- Congressman!

814
00:54:24,594 --> 00:54:28,722
- I think they want me to save them!
- Save them from what, Congressman?

815
00:54:28,848 --> 00:54:32,184
Saving the animals, okay.
I can roll with that. That's a good idea.

816
00:54:39,943 --> 00:54:40,985
The flood.

817
00:54:41,361 --> 00:54:43,862
A flood? Rolling out.

818
00:54:44,364 --> 00:54:45,698
The flood.

819
00:54:45,782 --> 00:54:47,908
This has been the hottest, driest summer
on record

820
00:54:47,993 --> 00:54:49,618
and you say we're going to have a flood?

821
00:54:49,703 --> 00:54:53,205
- When might we expect this?
- September 22, midday.

822
00:54:57,127 --> 00:55:00,713
- That's what I was told.
- Might I ask who told you?

823
00:55:07,554 --> 00:55:11,181
Not in front of all those people.
Don't say it. Don't say it.

824
00:55:16,479 --> 00:55:17,813
God.

825
00:55:22,610 --> 00:55:27,323
- God? You talk to God?
- Yes.

826
00:55:27,407 --> 00:55:32,077
And God is talking back?
- Yeah. We hung out a little.

827
00:55:32,454 --> 00:55:34,747
Well, time to update the rsum.

828
00:55:34,831 --> 00:55:37,207
Congressman, your name is being removed
from this bill.

829
00:55:37,292 --> 00:55:40,711
Obviously, the stresses of this office
have proven too much for you.

830
00:55:40,795 --> 00:55:44,089
- Please have the congressman removed.
- No. Please! You don't understand!

831
00:55:44,174 --> 00:55:46,967
God commanded me to build an ark!

832
00:55:47,052 --> 00:55:49,636
It's going to rain!
There's going to be a flood!

833
00:55:51,097 --> 00:55:55,059
- Remove him now!
- We have to prepare ourselves!

834
00:55:55,143 --> 00:55:57,853
I need to finish the ark!

835
00:55:59,064 --> 00:56:01,398
Remove him now!

836
00:56:07,655 --> 00:56:10,282
Does this mean we're moving back home?

837
00:56:10,575 --> 00:56:13,327
Home, Canada. One or the other.

838
00:56:23,797 --> 00:56:28,675
Joan? I know you probably saw
what happened, but I can explain.

839
00:56:32,931 --> 00:56:36,308
Take the stuff to the car, guys.
I'll be there in a minute.

840
00:56:38,561 --> 00:56:39,686
Guys?

841
00:56:43,274 --> 00:56:48,320
I'm gonna take them to my mother's.
Evan, I think you need help.

842
00:56:48,905 --> 00:56:53,700
Joan, please. I'm not doing this.
It's not me. It's him.

843
00:56:53,785 --> 00:56:57,079
I went to that meeting in a suit,
and he took it off of me.

844
00:56:57,163 --> 00:57:00,916
Those animals are following me
because of him.

845
00:57:01,000 --> 00:57:04,628
God?
Does God know he's destroying our lives?

846
00:57:04,712 --> 00:57:07,256
Does God know
he's going to get you fired?

847
00:57:07,340 --> 00:57:09,842
Yeah! He's trying to get me fired!

848
00:57:09,926 --> 00:57:13,053
He is trying to get me fired!

849
00:57:13,138 --> 00:57:15,305
That way I'll have more time
to work on the ark!

850
00:57:15,390 --> 00:57:17,891
Because the rain
and the floods are coming.

851
00:57:17,976 --> 00:57:21,395
No, I heard you, Evan.
The whole world heard you.

852
00:57:21,479 --> 00:57:24,106
Joan, please, you gotta believe me.

853
00:57:26,568 --> 00:57:31,363
There it is! It's happening!
It's happening! It's raining!

854
00:57:48,882 --> 00:57:50,382
Goodbye, Evan.

855
00:57:53,720 --> 00:57:54,845
Joan!

856
00:58:03,605 --> 00:58:08,192
I know! I know. Whatever you do,
you do because you love me!

857
00:58:15,950 --> 00:58:18,785
Do me a favor. Love me less.

858
00:58:20,163 --> 00:58:21,205
Congressman!

859
00:58:21,289 --> 00:58:24,249
Are you concerned at all
about Congressman Baxter's tirade

860
00:58:24,334 --> 00:58:26,001
and the adverse effects it may have
on your bill?

861
00:58:26,085 --> 00:58:29,838
The day it rains and floods and
Congressman Baxter takes a ride on his ark,

862
00:58:29,923 --> 00:58:31,924
that'll be the day I'll be concerned.
Thank you.

863
00:58:37,013 --> 00:58:41,350
His name is Evan Baxter,
but now he goes by "New York's Noah,"

864
00:58:41,434 --> 00:58:45,103
"Heaven's Evan,"
"The Weirdo with a Beardo. "

865
00:58:50,109 --> 00:58:53,779
Okay, guys. Watch it. Watch it.
Coming through. Watch your back.

866
00:58:55,323 --> 00:58:59,117
Marty, will you comment on Congressman
Baxter's change of appearance?

867
00:58:59,369 --> 00:59:03,205
Yes, his hair is long.
Yes, his beard is unshaven.

868
00:59:03,289 --> 00:59:05,499
Are you equally stunned
by this man's appearance?

869
00:59:11,923 --> 00:59:13,090
The way things go around here,

870
00:59:13,174 --> 00:59:15,968
if he gets any crazier,
we may end up in the White House.

871
00:59:22,308 --> 00:59:24,977
Hey! No, no, no! That's my cup!

872
00:59:26,521 --> 00:59:27,854
Whatever.

873
00:59:48,668 --> 00:59:52,129
He's filling the boat
with two of every kind of animal.

874
00:59:52,213 --> 00:59:55,507
Still to be collected,
two giraffes, two elephants

875
00:59:56,634 --> 00:59:58,468
and one more jackass.

876
01:00:01,681 --> 01:00:04,141
- What an idiot.
- He's a mook.

877
01:00:04,225 --> 01:00:05,642
Jerks.

878
01:00:06,394 --> 01:00:09,021
Don't worry about it, you guys.
Come on, eat up.

879
01:00:09,105 --> 01:00:11,356
- Not hungry.
- Yeah, me neither.

880
01:00:11,441 --> 01:00:13,734
You guys can't eat. I can't stop.

881
01:00:13,818 --> 01:00:15,736
- Can I go to the bathroom?
- Me, too?

882
01:00:15,820 --> 01:00:19,698
- Okay. Dylan, go with them. Please?
- Fine.

883
01:00:22,410 --> 01:00:26,038
- Excuse me. Can I get a refill, please?
- Coming right up.

884
01:00:27,123 --> 01:00:28,123
Thank you.

885
01:00:28,207 --> 01:00:31,335
- Excuse me. Are you all right?
- Yeah.

886
01:00:33,630 --> 01:00:37,049
- No. It's a long story.
- Well, I like stories.

887
01:00:37,967 --> 01:00:41,011
I'm considered a bit of a storyteller myself.

888
01:00:42,055 --> 01:00:45,182
My husband...
Have you heard of "New York's Noah"?

889
01:00:46,768 --> 01:00:49,853
- The guy who's building the ark.
- That's him.

890
01:00:49,937 --> 01:00:53,065
I love that story, Noah and the Ark.

891
01:00:53,149 --> 01:00:54,733
You know, a lot of people miss the point
of that story.

892
01:00:54,817 --> 01:00:57,402
They think it's about God's wrath and anger.

893
01:00:57,737 --> 01:01:02,032
- They love it when God gets angry.
- What is the story about, then? The ark?

894
01:01:02,116 --> 01:01:07,496
Well, I think it's a love story
about believing in each other.

895
01:01:07,580 --> 01:01:13,293
You know, the animals showed up in pairs.
They stood by each other, side by side,

896
01:01:13,378 --> 01:01:17,673
just like Noah and his family.
Everybody entered the ark side by side.

897
01:01:18,758 --> 01:01:21,635
But my husband says God told him to do it.

898
01:01:23,429 --> 01:01:26,932
- What do you do with that?
- Sounds like an opportunity.

899
01:01:29,936 --> 01:01:32,187
Let me ask you something.

900
01:01:32,271 --> 01:01:36,024
If someone prays for patience,
you think God gives them patience?

901
01:01:36,109 --> 01:01:39,403
Or does he give them
the opportunity to be patient?

902
01:01:41,114 --> 01:01:43,115
If they pray for courage,
does God give them courage,

903
01:01:43,199 --> 01:01:46,535
or does he give them opportunities
to be courageous?

904
01:01:47,995 --> 01:01:51,540
If someone prayed
for their family to be closer,

905
01:01:51,624 --> 01:01:55,335
you think God zaps them
with warm, fuzzy feelings?

906
01:01:55,420 --> 01:01:58,880
Or does he give them opportunities
to love each other?

907
01:02:01,050 --> 01:02:05,137
Well, I got to run.
A lot of people to serve. Enjoy.

908
01:02:12,145 --> 01:02:15,188
Guess this comes as no surprise to
those who remember his campaign promise,

909
01:02:15,273 --> 01:02:17,023
"I will lower taxes,

910
01:02:17,483 --> 01:02:19,651
"go crazy and build a gigantic ark. "

911
01:02:27,702 --> 01:02:29,703
Oh, my gosh.

912
01:02:34,542 --> 01:02:36,585
Evan!
- Dad?

913
01:02:36,669 --> 01:02:38,795
- Honey!
- Dad?

914
01:02:38,880 --> 01:02:41,047
You guys, I'm up here.

915
01:02:57,815 --> 01:02:59,816
- Rough week?
You look really funny.

916
01:02:59,901 --> 01:03:03,236
- You look really old.
- Yeah, well, he is really old.

917
01:03:04,989 --> 01:03:07,532
- Why'd you come back?
- It was the kids.

918
01:03:07,617 --> 01:03:10,619
- Tell him, guys.
- We like you better as the crazy guy.

919
01:03:10,703 --> 01:03:13,038
You spend time with us
and you're home a lot more.

920
01:03:13,122 --> 01:03:16,249
Just, please don't make us do
the dance anymore.

921
01:03:37,355 --> 01:03:41,817
I don't know what's going on,
or what you're going through,

922
01:03:42,568 --> 01:03:48,240
but we got into this as a family
and we're gonna get out of it as a family,

923
01:03:49,158 --> 01:03:50,826
side by side.

924
01:03:58,251 --> 01:04:01,670
But, Evan, we have to talk about the ark.
It has to come down.

925
01:04:01,754 --> 01:04:04,631
- I can't do that.
- You don't have a choice.

926
01:04:05,007 --> 01:04:08,426
Congressman Long went to the city.
There's a laundry list of code violations.

927
01:04:08,594 --> 01:04:11,012
You have until September 22
to take it down,

928
01:04:11,097 --> 01:04:13,014
or they'll take it down and arrest you.

929
01:04:13,099 --> 01:04:16,601
- September 22. That's the day of the flood.
- Mom! Dad! Come here!

930
01:04:41,752 --> 01:04:44,212
Don't you dare take that ark down.

931
01:04:46,799 --> 01:04:48,675
How are we gonna do this?

932
01:04:48,759 --> 01:04:51,011
There's no way the five
of us can finish on time.

933
01:04:51,095 --> 01:04:53,138
We don't have money to hire anybody else.

934
01:04:58,269 --> 01:05:00,228
Is that a llama with a hammer?

935
01:05:00,313 --> 01:05:04,399
An alpaca. They rarely spit at people
unless frightened or abused.

936
01:05:06,235 --> 01:05:08,194
Let's finish this sucker.

937
01:05:12,783 --> 01:05:13,909
Come on, let's go.

938
01:05:13,993 --> 01:05:15,410
No one knows where they came from

939
01:05:15,494 --> 01:05:17,287
or how the congressman is getting them
to do it,

940
01:05:17,371 --> 01:05:23,251
but, two by two, animals of all kinds
are working with Godspeed to build this ark.

941
01:05:23,336 --> 01:05:24,836
Thank you.

942
01:05:24,921 --> 01:05:28,131
If this flood really does happen,
"Evan help us. "

943
01:05:29,759 --> 01:05:31,509
Hey! A little help?

944
01:05:35,264 --> 01:05:36,306
Thanks.

945
01:05:37,683 --> 01:05:38,683
Here it is, hon.

946
01:05:40,102 --> 01:05:42,854
Perfect. Thanks.

947
01:05:46,734 --> 01:05:48,234
Hold it right there.

948
01:05:48,319 --> 01:05:51,905
This is Ed Carson coming to you live
from New York Noah's construction site,

949
01:05:51,989 --> 01:05:57,077
where we are unable to leave the news van
due to hazardous conditions outside.

950
01:06:00,206 --> 01:06:01,206
- High five.
- High five.

951
01:06:01,290 --> 01:06:02,290
Good job.

952
01:06:02,959 --> 01:06:04,668
Hey, putty tat.

953
01:06:08,714 --> 01:06:11,549
Go, go, go! He tried to eat me!

954
01:06:11,842 --> 01:06:14,552
Dylan! Jordan! Check it out!
Your mom's building an ark!

955
01:06:14,637 --> 01:06:15,971
Let's do the dance.

956
01:06:16,055 --> 01:06:18,056
No, please, no.

957
01:06:20,726 --> 01:06:22,644
Well, where did
the animals come from, then?

958
01:06:22,728 --> 01:06:25,313
Please. It's a trick.
It's a circus is what it is.

959
01:06:25,398 --> 01:06:28,483
Wild animals running amok
in suburban Virginia.

960
01:06:28,567 --> 01:06:32,404
With all these species,
what's being done about the feces?

961
01:06:38,411 --> 01:06:43,665
Evan Baxter! You have gone from newsman
to congressman to caveman.

962
01:06:43,749 --> 01:06:46,543
What makes you so sure God chose you?

963
01:06:47,503 --> 01:06:49,254
He chose all of us.

964
01:06:58,681 --> 01:07:00,557
Time to wash up, you guys.

965
01:07:07,148 --> 01:07:08,356
Thanks.

966
01:07:11,777 --> 01:07:13,278
You want some?

967
01:07:33,507 --> 01:07:36,634
Why couldn't
the man just buy a Corvette?

968
01:07:36,719 --> 01:07:40,930
Well, well, well. There they are.
It is good to see you guys.

969
01:07:41,015 --> 01:07:46,061
It's good to see you! Your hair looks great.
It's very regal. Man, I love your hair!

970
01:07:46,145 --> 01:07:47,729
And you're still sucking up.

971
01:07:47,813 --> 01:07:49,856
- So, why are you here?
- Long locked us out.

972
01:07:49,940 --> 01:07:50,940
He can't do that.

973
01:07:51,025 --> 01:07:53,234
I mean, I've been suspended,
but I'm still a congressman.

974
01:07:53,319 --> 01:07:55,570
- Rita, tell him what you know.
- Tell me what?

975
01:07:55,654 --> 01:07:58,406
I smelled a rat
the second we got that office.

976
01:07:58,491 --> 01:08:00,575
You don't get an office like that
for nothing.

977
01:08:00,659 --> 01:08:04,954
- So I had the stalker here do some research.
- Okay, Eugene, talk.

978
01:08:05,081 --> 01:08:07,290
Prestige Crest used to be federal lands,

979
01:08:07,500 --> 01:08:10,001
but what's interesting is
how it got into private hands.

980
01:08:10,294 --> 01:08:12,629
Congressman Long got the approval
to build a dam

981
01:08:12,713 --> 01:08:15,632
and then passed out the surrounding lands
to a group of private investors.

982
01:08:15,716 --> 01:08:17,050
Now, the locals fought this thing for years.

983
01:08:17,134 --> 01:08:19,385
They said Long and his developer buddies
were cutting corners,

984
01:08:19,470 --> 01:08:21,721
like skipping important building code
checkpoints.

985
01:08:21,806 --> 01:08:24,891
And with the land use bill, he's gonna do
the same thing with the national parks.

986
01:08:24,975 --> 01:08:28,645
So, you stand by and shake your pom-poms
while Long and his buddies get rich.

987
01:08:28,729 --> 01:08:30,855
What can we do? I'm suspended.

988
01:08:30,940 --> 01:08:34,359
Go back to the Hill and show them
that you can and will fight this bill.

989
01:08:34,443 --> 01:08:37,403
You guys, I'm sorry. I can't do that.
I have to get back to the ark.

990
01:08:37,488 --> 01:08:39,155
The ark? All right. Okay.

991
01:08:39,240 --> 01:08:41,157
- God told you to build an ark?
- Yes.

992
01:08:41,242 --> 01:08:44,285
But did he tell you to make your friends
believe in you and follow you here

993
01:08:44,370 --> 01:08:48,581
so you can make us look stupid?
'Cause I go to church every Sunday.

994
01:08:48,666 --> 01:08:50,917
Okay, every other Sunday.

995
01:08:51,001 --> 01:08:54,462
I've been to church!
And that does not sound like God to me.

996
01:08:54,547 --> 01:08:56,923
Rita, I know
that this doesn't make any sense.

997
01:08:57,007 --> 01:08:59,676
I just want you to trust me.
You just have to have faith.

998
01:08:59,760 --> 01:09:04,389
Evan, faith will not fight this bill.
The CINPLAN vote is today!

999
01:09:04,473 --> 01:09:08,184
If we're going to stop this thing,
you need to get down to Capitol Hill now!

1000
01:09:08,269 --> 01:09:12,564
- Otherwise, it's impossible!
- Dad, Dad, I think it's done.

1001
01:10:11,123 --> 01:10:15,376
What in the world?
I can't even get my cat to use the litter box.

1002
01:10:56,794 --> 01:11:01,214
It's September 22, and we're all still here.

1003
01:11:01,298 --> 01:11:02,799
Awkward!

1004
01:11:02,883 --> 01:11:06,261
People! The flood is imminent!

1005
01:11:06,345 --> 01:11:11,474
- Board the ark! Save yourselves!
Get down, you fool!

1006
01:11:11,976 --> 01:11:15,937
Listen to me! The time has come!

1007
01:11:16,021 --> 01:11:20,108
No, Captain Ahab! Your time has come!

1008
01:11:21,402 --> 01:11:26,114
Yeah, Baxter! The weather's 70 and sunny
with a chance of crazy!

1009
01:11:31,537 --> 01:11:37,583
- Do you hear that? The rains are upon us!
- Dad, I don't think that's the rains.

1010
01:11:42,006 --> 01:11:44,632
Hey, Baxter! Kiss your ark goodbye!

1011
01:11:57,229 --> 01:11:59,564
- Where is he?
- On the boat, sir.

1012
01:12:00,232 --> 01:12:02,358
Give me a minute.
Lets see if I can convince "Noah"

1013
01:12:02,443 --> 01:12:04,610
that the world doesn't have to end today.

1014
01:12:08,324 --> 01:12:11,326
I gotta hand it to you,
this is quite the show.

1015
01:12:11,410 --> 01:12:14,454
According to my source,
the show hasn't even started yet.

1016
01:12:14,538 --> 01:12:16,205
Still expecting the big flood.

1017
01:12:16,290 --> 01:12:18,541
You know, voters don't respond
to the gloom and doom stuff.

1018
01:12:18,625 --> 01:12:21,794
- They like a more positive message.
- Like the one you're sending with your bill?

1019
01:12:21,879 --> 01:12:23,838
How much did you make off of all this land?

1020
01:12:23,922 --> 01:12:27,175
You are destroying
our national parks for profit.

1021
01:12:27,259 --> 01:12:29,135
You have a problem
with somebody taking a little profit?

1022
01:12:29,219 --> 01:12:30,762
It's called business, son.

1023
01:12:30,846 --> 01:12:33,348
So if I need to get a message out there,
or get a congressman elected

1024
01:12:33,432 --> 01:12:37,477
there are people who pay for it, and yes,
those people want this bill to happen

1025
01:12:37,561 --> 01:12:41,647
and, by God, it's gonna happen.
Now you look down there.

1026
01:12:42,274 --> 01:12:44,025
Those are the wolves, son.

1027
01:12:44,109 --> 01:12:47,195
I'm gonna give you one last chance.
Take down this boat.

1028
01:12:47,279 --> 01:12:51,032
I'm giving you one last chance. Repent.

1029
01:12:52,284 --> 01:12:56,204
Such a shame. You had possibilities.

1030
01:12:56,288 --> 01:13:00,166
But you want to stop progress
to save the Earth. Go for it.

1031
01:13:00,250 --> 01:13:03,211
Good luck getting a tree
to come to the polls.

1032
01:13:08,133 --> 01:13:09,634
Take it down.

1033
01:13:16,934 --> 01:13:20,144
This is a court order
approving the demolition of this boat!

1034
01:13:20,229 --> 01:13:23,231
Evacuate immediately!
You have three minutes!

1035
01:13:25,901 --> 01:13:30,113
Honey. We have to go.
They're going to destroy the boat.

1036
01:13:30,864 --> 01:13:32,031
No.

1037
01:13:33,075 --> 01:13:34,992
It can't end this way.

1038
01:13:36,328 --> 01:13:40,331
Is it too much to ask
for a little precipitation?

1039
01:13:41,500 --> 01:13:45,253
Honey, maybe God didn't mean
a literal flood.

1040
01:13:45,337 --> 01:13:50,633
Maybe he meant a flood of knowledge
or emotion or awareness.

1041
01:13:50,717 --> 01:13:52,301
If that's true,

1042
01:13:53,220 --> 01:13:56,431
I am going to be so pissed.

1043
01:13:56,515 --> 01:13:57,765
Two minutes!

1044
01:13:57,850 --> 01:14:01,269
Get off the boat now
or you will be removed by force.

1045
01:14:01,353 --> 01:14:04,897
Evan, you did it. You built the ark.

1046
01:14:04,982 --> 01:14:07,942
- That's all you were asked to do, right?
- No.

1047
01:14:08,026 --> 01:14:12,238
There's something else.
Something's going to happen. I can feel it.

1048
01:14:12,322 --> 01:14:15,116
Yeah, what's gonna happen is
tear gas and a wrecking ball.

1049
01:14:15,200 --> 01:14:17,201
Evan, think of the kids.

1050
01:14:18,287 --> 01:14:19,704
One minute!

1051
01:14:21,915 --> 01:14:25,501
- Dad, whatever you say, I'm with you.
- Yeah, me, too.

1052
01:14:25,586 --> 01:14:27,670
Me, too.
But can we keep some of the animals?

1053
01:14:27,754 --> 01:14:30,006
I like the alpaca. He spits.

1054
01:14:34,511 --> 01:14:37,847
You're right. We did it. We built the boat.

1055
01:14:38,223 --> 01:14:39,223
Yeah.

1056
01:14:40,225 --> 01:14:42,643
Let's go. Let's go, guys. Come on.

1057
01:14:55,741 --> 01:14:57,450
Well, I guess they don't want to go.

1058
01:14:57,534 --> 01:15:00,620
- It's their instinct.
- What do you mean, hon?

1059
01:15:00,704 --> 01:15:05,458
Some animals know when weather's coming.
When they feel it coming, they sit.

1060
01:15:13,592 --> 01:15:14,717
Joan!

1061
01:15:24,102 --> 01:15:26,646
Okay. Time's up! We're coming in!

1062
01:15:26,730 --> 01:15:29,941
Get that ball in position!
We're clearing them out!

1063
01:15:40,869 --> 01:15:44,163
Is that rain? It's raining.

1064
01:15:44,248 --> 01:15:46,791
Lucky guess, Baxter. Lucky guess.

1065
01:16:03,308 --> 01:16:07,562
Looks like the drought's finally over.
Good news, eh, Congressman?

1066
01:16:07,646 --> 01:16:09,814
Yeah. Good news.

1067
01:16:12,276 --> 01:16:17,822
Everybody! Please! Get on the ark!

1068
01:16:19,825 --> 01:16:21,325
Go to the car!

1069
01:16:21,410 --> 01:16:25,496
Please! Everyone! On the ark!

1070
01:16:25,581 --> 01:16:28,916
Cover me up! Keep me dry!
Cover me up! Keep me dry!

1071
01:16:29,001 --> 01:16:33,004
Who's crazy now, huh?
Look at us all squishing!

1072
01:16:41,138 --> 01:16:43,973
- It kind of stopped raining.
- Is that it?

1073
01:16:44,057 --> 01:16:46,475
What did I tell you? It's fine. It's over.

1074
01:16:46,560 --> 01:16:48,644
Hey, Ahab! This is it?

1075
01:16:49,271 --> 01:16:51,814
Your God experiencing
a little water shortage?

1076
01:16:53,025 --> 01:16:56,652
It would appear Evan Baxter
was right about the rain,

1077
01:16:56,737 --> 01:17:00,239
with a slight miscalculation
as to the quantity.

1078
01:17:04,328 --> 01:17:07,538
- Something's wrong.
- Honey, the clouds are moving away.

1079
01:17:07,623 --> 01:17:10,625
No, no. No, this isn't right.

1080
01:17:11,460 --> 01:17:14,837
Evan, even if it kept raining,
it's not like it could cause a flood in a day.

1081
01:17:14,921 --> 01:17:20,176
But today is the day! It has to be.
This just doesn't make any sense!

1082
01:17:22,137 --> 01:17:24,347
- Wait a second.
- What is it?

1083
01:17:24,431 --> 01:17:28,100
Marty said that Long cut corners,
violated building codes.

1084
01:17:28,185 --> 01:17:30,728
- What are you talking about?
- The lake, Long Lake.

1085
01:17:30,812 --> 01:17:34,732
It's named after him.
It's the lake! It's the lake!

1086
01:17:47,913 --> 01:17:49,246
Oh, no.

1087
01:17:51,083 --> 01:17:55,795
Get on the ark! Everyone, on the ark now!

1088
01:17:55,879 --> 01:17:57,713
I think we should get on the ark.

1089
01:17:57,798 --> 01:18:00,633
I agree.
I think we should get on the ark also.

1090
01:18:00,717 --> 01:18:04,345
I'm cold. I'm wet. I'm going home.

1091
01:18:11,269 --> 01:18:13,437
Ladies first! Move!

1092
01:18:21,321 --> 01:18:24,949
Oh, my God. This is happening.
This is really happening.

1093
01:18:26,034 --> 01:18:29,370
Holy... Get everyone on the ark now!

1094
01:18:29,454 --> 01:18:32,081
Get on the ark now! Let's go!
Get on the ark! Let's go!

1095
01:18:32,165 --> 01:18:35,042
Go, go, go! Get on the ark!

1096
01:18:36,712 --> 01:18:40,840
Go, go, go! On the ark! Go, go, go!

1097
01:18:40,924 --> 01:18:43,384
All right, boys! Let's go! Let's go!

1098
01:18:43,468 --> 01:18:47,012
We're gonna need a bigger boat.
Stay here with the kids.

1099
01:18:56,148 --> 01:18:57,982
Come on, Rita!

1100
01:18:58,066 --> 01:19:02,236
Everyone, up the ramp! Onto the deck!
Come on! Hurry, hurry, hurry!

1101
01:19:02,320 --> 01:19:06,157
- Dylan, get back inside! It's too dangerous.
- No, Dad. I told you, I'm with you.

1102
01:19:10,537 --> 01:19:13,330
Careful, everyone.
In the ark! In the ark!

1103
01:19:13,415 --> 01:19:15,499
Watch your step! Up the ramp, everybody!

1104
01:19:23,759 --> 01:19:25,718
- Guys, help me with the door!
- Get the door! Get the door!

1105
01:20:08,887 --> 01:20:10,429
Guys! Guys!

1106
01:20:43,421 --> 01:20:45,172
Everybody hang on!

1107
01:20:56,601 --> 01:20:58,769
You guys all right? You okay?

1108
01:20:59,396 --> 01:21:00,938
There's been a flood at Prestige Crest

1109
01:21:01,022 --> 01:21:03,190
and you're seeing live images
of New York Noah's ark

1110
01:21:03,275 --> 01:21:06,485
caught in the storm surge
and heading towards Memorial Bridge!

1111
01:21:14,327 --> 01:21:16,871
We're going to crash!
Turn this thing around!

1112
01:21:16,955 --> 01:21:19,790
We're not gonna make it!
Save us, Baxter!

1113
01:21:31,511 --> 01:21:36,098
I command thee halt! Stop! Whoa!

1114
01:21:36,182 --> 01:21:37,850
It's not working!

1115
01:21:38,643 --> 01:21:41,395
How about a little help here?

1116
01:22:27,233 --> 01:22:29,735
What do you mean there was water damage?
It rained for ten minutes.

1117
01:22:29,819 --> 01:22:31,612
That is not possible.

1118
01:22:41,247 --> 01:22:43,123
- I love you guys.
- All right.

1119
01:22:43,208 --> 01:22:44,458
- Seriously.
- Okay, I got it.

1120
01:22:44,542 --> 01:22:45,668
- I love you.
- Thank you.

1121
01:23:03,144 --> 01:23:07,731
All those in favor of the Public
Land Act, please signify by saying, "Aye. "

1122
01:23:14,823 --> 01:23:16,115
Good God!

1123
01:23:51,443 --> 01:23:52,860
I think we can walk from here.

1124
01:24:11,129 --> 01:24:15,758
Hello, Congressman.
Mind if I park my boat here for a little while?

1125
01:24:16,843 --> 01:24:18,927
- But how...
- The dam, Congressman.

1126
01:24:19,012 --> 01:24:22,556
Your reservoir ruptured.
Prestige Crest, it's all gone.

1127
01:24:22,640 --> 01:24:25,184
No. They said that couldn't happen.

1128
01:24:26,227 --> 01:24:27,936
I never thought this...

1129
01:24:28,813 --> 01:24:33,692
You. You did this to me.
You set me up, you crazy son of a...

1130
01:24:37,030 --> 01:24:39,364
Wow. That is disgusting.

1131
01:24:39,824 --> 01:24:41,241
If that comes out your front,

1132
01:24:41,326 --> 01:24:44,745
I don't even want to know
what's coming out the back.

1133
01:24:47,999 --> 01:24:50,542
Don't look down, Congressman,
but the wolves are here,

1134
01:24:50,627 --> 01:24:54,546
although I wouldn't worry so much
about these wolves as those.

1135
01:25:02,847 --> 01:25:04,223
Gesundheit.

1136
01:25:16,319 --> 01:25:19,947
As you can see behind me,
New York Noah's prediction came true.

1137
01:25:20,031 --> 01:25:22,533
The vote of the Land Act Bill
has been suspended,

1138
01:25:22,617 --> 01:25:25,452
pending investigation of Congressman Long
for profiteering...

1139
01:25:25,537 --> 01:25:28,497
Of course now, the question is,
how will these animals be returned

1140
01:25:28,581 --> 01:25:30,124
to their natural habitats?

1141
01:25:30,208 --> 01:25:34,086
Something tells me, if God got them here,
he can probably get them home.

1142
01:25:34,170 --> 01:25:37,214
The House will undoubtedly
reinstate Congressman Baxter

1143
01:25:37,298 --> 01:25:39,049
when it reconvenes in the morning.

1144
01:25:39,134 --> 01:25:42,970
Until then, there is a lot to be done here
on Capitol Hill.

1145
01:25:43,054 --> 01:25:45,139
How's Buster doing?
Come on, Buster.

1146
01:25:45,223 --> 01:25:47,599
No, come on. Come on!
Come on!

1147
01:25:47,684 --> 01:25:49,476
These too heavy? It's all right?
No, it's fine.

1148
01:25:49,561 --> 01:25:51,979
He can't keep up.
- I know, sweetie!

1149
01:25:52,063 --> 01:25:55,274
All right.
What do you say we take a little break?

1150
01:25:55,358 --> 01:25:56,984
We've only been walking
for, like, five minutes, Dad.

1151
01:25:57,068 --> 01:26:00,279
Well, five on, five off.
Life is about balance, right?

1152
01:26:00,363 --> 01:26:01,655
- How about some sandwiches?
- Okay.

1153
01:26:01,739 --> 01:26:04,616
- Who wants sandwiches? Let's do it!
I get first dibs!

1154
01:26:04,701 --> 01:26:06,994
Everyone but Buster
is going to get a sandwich.

1155
01:26:07,078 --> 01:26:11,456
You do not get a sandwich! You're a dog
and you do not get a sandwich!

1156
01:26:11,541 --> 01:26:14,751
Buster is part of the family now.
You're just gonna have to get used to it.

1157
01:26:14,836 --> 01:26:16,670
Poor Buster!

1158
01:26:17,422 --> 01:26:20,507
Honey, come here.
Sweetheart, be careful. Come here.

1159
01:26:20,592 --> 01:26:22,509
- Hey, hon, save me one, okay?
- Okay.

1160
01:26:22,594 --> 01:26:24,344
I'll be right back.

1161
01:26:32,353 --> 01:26:33,729
- Hey.
- Hey.

1162
01:26:35,607 --> 01:26:37,566
What are you doing here?

1163
01:26:37,859 --> 01:26:40,277
Just hanging out with some old friends.

1164
01:26:40,361 --> 01:26:43,655
You knew all along, didn't you?
You knew the dam was unstable.

1165
01:26:43,740 --> 01:26:47,576
If it hadn't been for the ark,
my family, the neighbors...

1166
01:26:47,660 --> 01:26:51,455
- I fought you every step of the way.
- Yes, but you did it.

1167
01:26:52,457 --> 01:26:57,002
So, you had nothing to do with the flood?
Like where the ark landed exactly?

1168
01:26:57,086 --> 01:27:00,547
I gave you a little shove at the end. Sue me.

1169
01:27:03,134 --> 01:27:06,845
You did good, son. You changed the world.

1170
01:27:06,930 --> 01:27:09,598
- No, no, I didn't.
- Well, let's see.

1171
01:27:09,682 --> 01:27:13,769
Spending time with your family,
making them very happy.

